The paper discusses the implementation of innovative library services into a document repository, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The mention of automatic keywording and reference extraction also suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and computational linguistics (cs.CY). The use of bibliometric tools and collaborative management tools could also indicate a focus on computer networks and communications (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the mention of e-science possibilities suggests a focus on scientific computing (cs.SC) and interdisciplinary applications (cs.SI).
